# 6001CEM Project - Student Dashboard Prototype

## Project Overview
This repository contains a prototype for the 6001CEM Individual Project by Taha Amir Khan (Student ID: 11651879). The project is designed as a Student Dashboard for Coventry University, integrating interactive UI elements such as modals, notifications, charts, a dynamic timetable, and document request functionality.

## Repository Contents
- index.html – Main HTML structure for the student dashboard.
- styles.css – CSS styles for layout, responsive design, and UI components.
- script.js – JavaScript handling modals, pop-ups, charts (via Chart.js), notifications, and other interactive features.
- coventry-logo.png – Coventry University logo used in the header.
- aula-logo.jpeg – Aula logo used in the coursework section.

## Features
- Student Dashboard Interface: A centralized portal with a modern, responsive design.
- Interactive Notifications: Real-time alerts via modals with clickable actions.
- Dynamic Timetable: Weekly schedule with room updates and class information.
- Document Requests: Generate and download student-related documents.
- Grade Overview: Interactive grade tables and academic progress visualization using doughnut charts.
- Support Services: Access extensive student support information.

## Technologies Used
- HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript.
- Chart.js for charting and data visualization.
- Font Awesome for icons.
- Responsive design with media queries for mobile compatibility.

## Deployment Instructions
1. Clone the repository:
   ```sh
   git clone https://github.com/your-github-username/repository-name.git
   ```
2. Open `index.html` in a web browser to launch the prototype.
3. Modify `styles.css` and `script.js` as needed for customization.

## Future Improvements
- Integrate a backend for real-time data and user authentication.
- Enhance accessibility and compliance with WCAG guidelines.
- Expand interactive features and modularize the JavaScript code for maintainability.
- Add real-time push notifications and advanced data analytics.

